JVCLInfo
  GROUP=JVCL.EditsMemosAndCombos.Other
  FLAG=Component
Summary
  Inspector control.
Description
  TJvInspector is an inspector control. The inspector control is responsible of displaying and
  navigating the data tree. The control is completely seperated from the editing layer and the
  editing layer is completely seperated from the data layer. This means the control is able to
  "inspect" a wide variaty of data types, without the need of creating a new descendant of the
  inspector control.
  It also means you can mix various data sources in one view.

  The control does not handle the painting itself. This is left
  to a painter object.
See Also
  $JVCL.Info.Inspector

